name: Faile - Serendipity - Letterpress Print Limited edition
description:
Formed in the late 1990’s from three founding members Patrick McNeil, Patrick Miller, and Aiko Nakagawa. Faile was an acknowledgement of the inevitable process of deterioration that an artwork suffered when exposed to the elements.

This is one of four of a series printed for Faile at Hatch Showprint in Nashville, TN. For those that don't know Hatch have been letterpress printmaking since 1875.

If you're a fan of printmaking techniques then these are a really great example, printed from somewhere with a lot of history.

These were produced in 2001. printed on heavy card

Measures 56cm x 36cm

description:

name: Shepard Fairey - Obey Giant - Motorhead - Limited edition-Red
description:
As most of you will know him from his iconic Obama image, for those of you that don't know Shepard started off with his Andre the Giant wheat pasting many moons ago. This is an original screen print pulled by the great man himself back in 2002 - hand screened on heavy cotton off white paper, twisting the iconic Motorhead skull, a beautiful collectors piece, there are only 3 available -  so if you want it - you're going to need to be quick!

name: Pinky - Helter Skelter Limited edition
description: We did our first ever show back in 2004 with Pinky. and what a show it was!! Amazing all round physcadelic dude Pinky started off his Graffiti career back in the day in Hull. Having done commissions as varied as the restaurant at Harvey Nicks for Justin Timberlake, to the graffiti for Ali G ( sorry dude!) and a whole bunch in between here is the limited edition screen print that we produced for the Best Pussy show in May of this year, printed on beautiful coloufast 250 gsm, signed and numbered by the artist in an edition of 50.

name: Claire Skully  - Wolf - Limited edition
description: Claire Skully is a lady full of talent - her birds and landscapes are beautiful, if not slightly spooky :) here is her blue/black wolf hand screened on beautiful off white 250 gsm paper, in a limited edition of 30. Signed and numbered by the artist.

name: Claire Skully  - Octopus - Limited edition
description: Claire Skully is a lady full of talent - her birds and landscapes are beautiful, if not slightly spooky :) here is her flourescent orange octopus hand screened on beautiful off white 250 gsm paper, in a limited edition of 30. Signed and numbered by the artist.

name: Antony Micallef - Pulling Sophie the Versace Girl -Limited edition Screen Print Will
description:
This is a rare chance to own what is known to be Antony Micallef's first Limited edition print publication. Pulling Sophie the Versace Girl was published in November 2004 By Dead Teen. It predates EyeStorm editions by over a year.

It was one of four works produced for a project entitled "Hurry Before You Die" and uniquely features a legally binding will on the reverse of the print. If you're brave, or famous (!) enough just fill in the detials and you can leave what you want to whom ever you choose.

The edition is of 40, and is numbered. It is a single colour hand -pulled screen print on heavy weight art paper and measures 25x19 inches.

We have 3 of these only.

name: CAP limited edition screen print
description:
This super rare screen print of the infamous CAP tag, comes from the Blood Wars exhibition held at ALife in NYC back in 2002. Printed on beautiful cotton rag paper, signed and numbered by the artist (artist?! I guess it depends on your point of view :) in a run of 150  only. For those that don't know CAP, he  was pretty much the most hated man in the NYC Graffiti scene  for a long time, going over everyone's work with his now infamous throw up - at least you can call him consistent.....:) 
measures 57.5 cm x 38.5 cm
Shipping is by Parcel Force 48hrs, insured and signed for.

name: Nick Walker - Nikers - Limited edition screenprint
description:
Nick Walker has been doing amazingly well these past couple of years, and here is one of his original screen prints, in the first colour way of olive and magenta. ( way before the larger run of black and white) This is number 2/100, so super rare. 

measures 59cm x 40cm

All prints are sent by parcelforce 48 in the UK - for overseas shipping please contact before purchasing.

name: Mode 2 - Size Does Not Matter- Limited edtition Screen Print
description:
Mode 2 needs no introduction. Simply one of the most influential graffiti artists there has ever been. A founding member of one of Europe's first serious graffiti crews, the Chrome Angelz, whose paintings had pride of place in Henry Chalfant and James Prigoff's Spraycan Art, he moved to Paris where he painted throughout the 90's with Parisian graffiti outfit 93 NTM. 
His lettering and crisp character paintings are world-famous. 

Edition of 69.

Printed on heavy cream stock. Signed and numbered by the artist. Published by Pictures on Walls.

Measures 64cm x 69 cm

Will be sent by Parcel force 48hrs insured and signed for. Overseas customers please contact for shipping prices.

name: Hiroshi Batbot flouro pink limited edition screen print

He also has great hair :)

Edition of 40

Measures 59cm x 42 cm

prints are sent by Parcel Force 48hrs, overseas buyers please email for shipping charges.

This is where he found all of his inspiration, and for the most part still does. busy doing graphics for Stussy, amongst other things, this one of the four prints done for the Monster Mash show, at the Intoxica Gallery in Notting Hill.

name: CEPT Spradio
description:
The very talented CEPT made this amazing little contraption...yes, it's an am/fm radio in a spraycan..no, really. And the big bonus is, it actually works!!! - headphones are handily stashed in the lid, and new batteries pop in the bottom, retractable ariel, and the on/off switch is the can's nozzle...yes, you just read that. wow.

There's only one, so please bare that in mind people.

name: Adam Sage - Bike - hand pulled lino print- ltd edt
description:
Adam Sage is a very talented tattooist and artist. Working out of world renowned tattoo studio Into-You, he works entirely by hand, no machines involved. He takes this to extreme levels when he does his amazing lino cut prints -  only ever making a few of each image, here is his homage to all things bike related ( dare I mention the word fixie? no, I thought not) 
No two are ever exactly the same, so really you're getting a piece of original art, not to mention a piece of Adam too...;)

Printed on heavy cotton paper only 8 printed of each

Signed and numbered by the artist
